Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.22,0:00:07.26,Music,,0,0,0,,♪ "Whole Lotta Love"\NLed Zeppelin
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.58,0:00:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello and welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Top Gear of the Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.16,0:00:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as I'm sure you know, Top of the Pops\Nwas killed off last year, but they wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.94,0:00:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring it back for this Comic Relief\Nspecial and we were given the job
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because our name is quite similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so what we've got in store is,\Nlike Top Gear, only half as long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.30,0:00:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of cars, there's music.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.40,0:00:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've got Supergrass,\Nwe've got Travis...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and then, at the end... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the show,\Nthe three of us will be performing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.82,0:00:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as a band for the very first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.76,0:00:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.18,0:01:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes!\N-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.46,0:01:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We could well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.74,0:01:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We could well set a record as the worst\Nband ever to appear on British television!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.58,0:01:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but that's then, this is now,\Nand we're kicking off tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.20,0:01:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with the latest single\Nfrom Lethal Bizzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:16.78,Music,,0,0,0,,♪ "Mr."\NLethal Bizzle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.62,0:01:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ {\i1}Yeah, it's Lethal the Bizzle records{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.38,0:01:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ It{\i1}'s Back to Bizznizz{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.10,0:01:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Fire Camp! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ It{\i1}'s Lethal the Bizzle records ♪\N♪ It's, it's Lethal the Bizzle records{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.94,0:01:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ {\i1}It's, it's Lethal the Bizzle records{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.64,0:01:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What the fuck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.10,0:01:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Hammond put him\Non at the wrong speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Imma take your girlfriend\Nand F your sister, mister ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.22,0:01:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You don't wanna play ♪\N♪ Mister, nah ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.10,0:01:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted to borrow a hoe!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.82,0:01:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe he's a farmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.54,0:01:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Who do you really\Never think you're talking to? ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.30,0:01:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ What do you really think\Nyou really wanna do? ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.30,0:01:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You don't wanna play ♪\N♪ Mister, nah ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.06,0:01:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ {\i1}You don't wanna play, mister{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.70,0:01:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ {\i1}You don't wanna play, mister{\i0} ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.86,0:01:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Imma take your\Ngirlfriend and F your sis- ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.42,0:01:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[SONG CUTS]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.38,0:02:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.10,0:02:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.22,0:02:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's noises like that that killed off\NTop of the Pops in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it wasn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.05,0:02:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.40,0:02:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They were saying "Oh, no-one's\Ninterested in the charts any more,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.58,0:02:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, Fearne Cotton's\Ndress isn't see-through",
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.74,0:02:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and afterwards, they kept\Nbooking acts like, what's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.10,0:02:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jizzy Tissue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.14,0:02:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lethal... Lethal Bizzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.98,0:02:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- After that rather truncated first song...\N- What have you got next?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.14,0:02:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone rolling a barrel\Nof spoons down some stairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.68,0:02:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.26,0:02:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, actually, almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's James May!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.18,0:02:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.58,0:02:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to liven up the old\NTop of the Pops format,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we've had an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.78,0:02:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to invite a band on and\Nwe're going to give them a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're going to ask them\Nto write an entire song from scratch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.54,0:02:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then perform it\Nat the end of the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.22,0:02:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and this sort of thing\Nwill require excellent songwriting skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,superb musicianship, so\Nwould you please welcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.98,0:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ladies and gentlemen, Mc... Fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Top Gear of the Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.90,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Now, look...\N- You can't be formal with a band!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.42,0:03:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.10,0:03:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a chance for you to prove\Nthat you're not just some useless,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.74,0:03:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,manufactured, dopey boy band.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.06,0:03:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's find out, because we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.82,0:03:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that you knew we were\Ngoing to ask you to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you've probably already\Nworked up a song, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't at all. I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.30,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to make absolutely\Nsure you can't cheat
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and, to be honest,\Nto bugger you up completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.98,0:03:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we've invented some rules.\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.82,0:03:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are three words that\Nyou can't use in writing your song.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.46,0:03:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.54,0:03:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Love,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Baby...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.58,0:03:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.50,0:03:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there are three words\Nthat you must use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:03:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:04:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sofa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Administration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.74,0:04:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hyundai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.70,0:04:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.42,0:04:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.78,0:04:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyundai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hyundai.\N- Absolutely, ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.74,0:04:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm looking forward to that.\N- How long do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.66,0:04:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you've got until the end\N of the show, so if I were you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.66,0:04:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd bugger off and get cracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyundai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.06,0:04:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't wait for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.92,0:04:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, here's a reminder\Nof why we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.80,0:04:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Comic Relief has spent years helping\Nteenagers who have run away from home and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,got into trouble with drink,\Ndrugs, and even prostitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.80,0:04:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we want to spend the money to stop\Nthis happening to help the runaways get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,home before the trouble begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.36,0:04:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Concern is growing for a 13-year-old girl\Nfrom Milton Keynes who's gone missing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.02,0:04:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Christy Jay Mahoney\Ndisappeared last Friday night{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i0}- Every day I used to think,\Nis she going to come home?{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.62,0:04:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Will she come back in one piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:04:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she going to come back in a black bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My initial first step, get posters\Nsplattered around Milton Keynes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bus stops, buses, up the city centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.64,0:05:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, it was just a\Ncase of just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.54,0:05:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to find my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Children who run away can find it hard to\Nring home for all sorts of reasons.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But they are in real danger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.70,0:05:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's why the Runaway Helpline\N has been set up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's for under 18s, it's confidential, and\Nthe operators understand what both{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}children and parents are going through.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.40,0:05:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They can help find children a safe place\Nto stay and can help them get back in{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}touch with their families.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day I'd be waiting\Non the phone to ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.34,0:05:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day was an agonising 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.66,0:05:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,After three long weeks, Christy Jay made the\Nmost important call of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.38,0:05:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She called her mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.20,0:06:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when I heard her little voice on\Nthe phone saying, ''Hi, Mum, it's me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,CJ.'' And I said, ''Where are you?''
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.82,0:06:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, ''I'll be home soon.''
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.26,0:06:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I saw\NChristy Jay at the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I just put my arms around her\Nand I didn't want to let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.74,0:06:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are vulnerable children out there\N on the streets tonight in danger,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}frightened, confused.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.06,0:06:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hope it's not your child.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But projects like the Runaway Helpline,\Nfunded by Comic Relief, are working now to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.24,0:06:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}keep these children safe and we\Nare asking you to help us to help them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.16,0:06:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Help bring families back together where we\Ncan and bring kids to safety before their{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.02,0:06:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}lives fall apart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:07:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To make a donation,\Ntelephone 08457 910 910 or you\Ncan log on to bbc.co.uk/rednoseday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.34,0:07:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.34,0:07:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's time for the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought what we'd do in\NTop Gear of The Pops is blend
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.62,0:07:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of musical news and motoring news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.94,0:07:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, we know cars...\N- Yes, Jeremy, we know cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.34,0:07:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know... iPods.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.26,0:07:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you plug an iPod into a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can.\NA Mercedes, you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.78,0:07:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can in a Mercedes, and you\N can even adjust it on the steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the vast majority of cars that I test,\Nyou can't just plug an iPod in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.02,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everybody's got an iPod these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody under 140 years old\Nhas got an iPod these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.54,0:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- They are everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.50,0:07:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- You've got to remember that the car\Nindustry took 50 years to work out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.78,0:07:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that a little light needed to\Ncome on when you opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wouldn't hold your breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.12,0:07:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, okay, right, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.34,0:07:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just make a plea\Nto the makers of iPods?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.18,0:07:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the wire thing, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.46,0:07:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You fold it up really neatly,\Nput it in your pocket, pull it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.98,0:07:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,one minute later,\Nit is a knot so complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. \N - I'm right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.14,0:08:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I've ended up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.10,0:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put your iPod on,\NI get the things...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.12,0:08:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just two huge knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.54,0:08:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I know exactly what\Nyou mean. It's immaculately neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull it out of your pocket\Nand you'll never undo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got one of your\Ntesticles tied up in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I've got a story\Nhere about Coldplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm really... I'm sorry,\Nbut I don't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this. "Fear not, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.42,0:08:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"they haven't gone emo for\Nthe follow-up to the mega 'X&Y'"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.74,0:08:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What the bloody hell does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- We work with this all the time. \N- It's rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.92,0:08:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things I thought we could do\Nin the news was talk about festivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.30,0:08:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Loads coming up this year, and\NI've got the line-ups from some of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.86,0:08:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's Hyde Park Calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.30,0:08:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got Aerosmith,\Npossibly the Rolling Stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.10,0:08:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,V Festival. Kasabian, The Fratellis,\NSnow Patrol, Basement Jaxx.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.52,0:08:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Worst band in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.82,0:08:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- What, Basement Jaxx? \N- Basement Jaxx.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, why Basement Jaxx? \N- No, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Worst band ever, ever, ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to go near a microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.38,0:09:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to hose them down\Nwith machine gun fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.02,0:09:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of them, James?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.70,0:09:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never had a Basement Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like talking to me dad\Nabout music when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.38,0:09:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to say, my dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.70,0:09:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My favourite one my dad did\Nwatching Top Of The Pops was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.22,0:09:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.02,0:09:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Billy Idol came on to do "White Wedding",\Nand he just looked and he went...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.26,0:09:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"He had a thought going on telly,\Nhe'd have put a shirt on."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.22,0:09:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you sound like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, but I have to say, most festivals\Nthese days, I think, are getting a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.38,0:09:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Glastonbury this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, what, presumably...\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.58,0:09:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in a Range Rover\Nwith a posh Fortnum's hamper?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.90,0:09:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm going in a helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.62,0:09:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, for crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.86,0:09:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How very, very festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.54,0:09:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But, no, we're going to land\Nduring the Arctic Monkeys,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.70,0:09:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and that'll improve it for everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here's a musical\Nfigure, Phil Spector,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.54,0:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a musical name, of course. He's on trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.86,0:09:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to be going on trial\Nfor murdering somebody called
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.90,0:09:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarkson.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.02,0:09:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all felt like that\Non occasions, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.18,0:09:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:09:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But he felt it was a good idea,\Nobviously, to convince the jury
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.22,0:10:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's not mental.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's the image he's gone for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[LAUGHS]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.82,0:10:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah, there\Nthey're going to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"No, I didn't do anything!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Right, no, of course he didn't".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.74,0:10:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, Jeremy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, all right, I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.00,0:10:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking of stuff\Nwe could talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.06,0:10:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lists, that's kind of appropriate, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of records and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I love a list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, well, a subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know hospital radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't, you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.22,0:10:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.78,0:10:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,..with your past in local radio DJing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a lot of DJs started there, it's relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've been thinking of a list of songs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.06,0:10:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can't play\Non your hospital radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.18,0:10:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one:\NThe Verve, "Drugs Don't Work".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- That'd be difficult to listen to.\N- Sure, you can't play that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.10,0:10:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Cutting Crew,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"I Could Have Died In Your Arms Tonight"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.68,0:10:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Fergal Sharkey, "A Good Heart"\Ncould be sensitive in certain wards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.70,0:10:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, for the transplant ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.82,0:10:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- That would not be...\N- A good heart is hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.02,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think about it, it's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:10:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a brilliant idea. Charts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:10:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good chart, innit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Top five records for playing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen the\Nnew Snow Patrol video?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.06,0:11:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.82,0:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, and remember "Rendez-vous"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.20,0:11:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.\N- That French film director, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.64,0:11:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And he got a bit of film left and he bolted\Nthe camera to the front of his Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.74,0:11:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,blasted through the streets of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.98,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- We showed it on Top Gear, didn't we?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.58,0:11:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they've put their new track\Nover the "Rendez-vous" video.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.10,0:11:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.18,0:11:22.94,Music,,0,0,0,,♪ "Open Your Eyes"\NSnow Patrol
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.60,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not a bad tune, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.26,0:11:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.80,0:11:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.58,0:11:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we just see the original of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I think the noise\Nin the original is better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's not a bad tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good tune. I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.42,0:11:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear the words\Nand everything, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Annoyingly, I think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A Ferrari V12 is better\Nthan Snow Patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.18,0:12:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Big trend at the moment,\N old supergroups reforming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.79,0:12:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis, The Police,\NVan Halen, apparently...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.55,0:12:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, Van Halen were going...\N- Or have they fall out again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they've fallen out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.94,0:12:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because modern music,\Nlike Jizzy Tissue that we had on earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.18,0:12:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is such rubbish that that's why\Nthe old ones are getting back to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's because old farts like you two
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.94,0:12:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,keep supporting all these\Nold bands full of old farts
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,at festivals in your helicopters,\Nand that's why they keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.21,0:12:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis is better than any modern band...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.38,0:12:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're not, they're old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You two start...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.26,0:12:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, well, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.11,0:12:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only saying you're old as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.82,0:12:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- She is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.95,0:12:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's inappropriate, unfortunately.\N- Why do you think that Genesis is back?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Phil Collins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil Collins is not Genesis, woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.77,0:12:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil Collins was one of the\Nbest drummers in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.18,0:12:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and on {\i1}Selling England by the Pound{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.70,0:12:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if you listen to "Firth of Fifth",\Nthe drumming in that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.14,0:12:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, there we go.\N- I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.14,0:12:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's started to ramble\Non about the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose you've heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel it coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.97,0:12:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, you're singing on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.58,0:12:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.18,0:13:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, that is the end\Nof the news. And now,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.18,0:13:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to say that it gives me\Ngreat pleasure to introduce the next band,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.31,0:13:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but since they're performing\Na new single we haven't heard yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows whether\Nit'll be a pleasure or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.86,0:13:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, ladies and gentlemen,\N please welcome, Travis!
