Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.66,0:17:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think that was a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Very, very tuneful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, anyway, it's time now\Nfor the charts from last week!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.47,0:17:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry we don't have this week's charts,\Nbut we're recording this live last Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.58,0:17:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.50,0:17:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,58)}At five, it's Fray, How To Save a Life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.06,0:17:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,58)}At four, Grace Kelly, with "MIKA".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,85)}At three, it's Akon\Nfeaturing The Sweet Escape,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.34,0:17:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,58)}performing "Gwen Stefani".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,58)}And at num...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I'm sorry, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.98,0:17:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.02,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I'll tell you what it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The only person who cares\Nhow many records Akon has sold...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.86,0:18:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is Akon. All we're bothered\Nabout, bearing in mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,how horrible modern music is\Nhow quickly they get the song over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've come up with\Na new chart, and here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.06,0:18:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At number three, it's Kelis featuring
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.66,0:18:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,someone with a name\Nthey weren't christened with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and "Lil Star" at\Nthree minutes, 14 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At number two, Grace Kelly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.38,0:18:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who didn't die in a car accident,\Nas we all suspected,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.82,0:18:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,with "MIKA". Three\Nminutes, eight seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fastest record\Nin the chart this last week was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.38,0:18:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Cascada, with "Miracle".\NTwo minutes, 46 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.98,0:18:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.18,0:18:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, time for another reminder\Nof why we're actually here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Somaliland, I took you on a\Nnightmare trip once there, to Hargeisa
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.17,0:18:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital, a hospital with no drugs, no\Nsurgical instruments, no sterile equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.47,0:19:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 2003, but you'd think I'd stepped\Ninto a Victorian horror story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.37,0:19:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People were turned away because there was\Nno drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.21,0:19:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,People were turned away from the hospital\Nbecause they had no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.39,0:19:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you ever wonder what happened to your\Nmoney?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it do any good?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.47,0:19:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it achieve anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.33,0:19:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.53,0:19:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.89,0:19:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm filming for Comic Relief in Kenya,\Nbut I've got hold of some footage that's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,just come over the border from Somaliland.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.23,0:19:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our pharmacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is... You can see all the drugs\Nare here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.21,0:19:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is from Comic Relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.75,0:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's remarkable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.55,0:19:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The drugs have done a lot of good things\Nin Hargeisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.41,0:19:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, everybody can get drugs whether they\Npay or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best thing I could have seen,\Nbecause the people who can't afford the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,drugs get them for nothing, which is\Nabsolutely brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.47,0:19:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You've set them up forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.67,0:19:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the biggest problems\Nfor the hospital was that people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't get there quickly\Nenough in an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And those first few minutes can mean the\Ndifference between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.10,0:20:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only ambulance was literally rusting\Ninto the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.61,0:20:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.21,0:20:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the ambulance all shiny with Comic Relief\Non the side and the old siren going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.07,0:20:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your money bought them a new ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.97,0:20:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference is absolutely staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.61,0:20:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm blown sideways by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.51,0:20:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the wards look a little more familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.37,0:20:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still in desperate need of some\Nserious attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just overwhelming to see all you've\Ndone for this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.59,0:20:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your money has provided drugs,\Na much needed ambulance, and it's helped
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,turn this hospital around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.91,0:20:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you've seen, that's just the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've still got a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,With your help, we can fix this ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can finish the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.37,0:21:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Without you, this terrifying thing\Nhappens.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.47,0:21:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.65,0:21:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, give us a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And give as much as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen what your money can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,08457 910 910.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.71,0:21:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or donate online at bbc.co.uk/rednoseday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.77,0:21:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can change and save lives today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.61,0:21:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Phone that number or we'll tell your\Nneighbours that you interfere with animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.14,0:21:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.21,0:21:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, now it's back to the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.34,0:21:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Our next band, the drummer...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.18,0:21:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,His dad used to be a presenter\Non Top Gear about 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris Goffey, you may remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.42,0:21:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, here they are,\Nwith Ade Edmondson on guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.06,0:21:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please welcome, Supergrass!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.99,0:21:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, chaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to glam this up visually, okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.30,0:21:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the three of us are going to be\Nproviding some special effects for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.14,0:22:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Hammond, are you ready on the wind?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.98,0:22:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.10,0:22:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,May, are you ready with\Nthe Bonnie Tyler doves?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.45,0:22:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, I'm on dry ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.06,0:22:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Start your tune!
